name: Kingston Park Raceway
slogan: Kingston Park Raceway is Queenslands premier go kart race track catering to private individuals, corporate events and party's. Go Hard, Go Fast, Go Karting
description:
Australia's Premier Go Karting Attraction

Kingston Park Raceway is Australia's largest and most technically advanced Go Karting & Amusement venue. The raceway has over 100 go karts and 3 great tracks to test the driver's skills.

There are 4 levels of go karts at Kingston Park Raceway, to suit varied levels of ability and experience. Families with Children can enjoy a day of fast fun and excitement in the Go Zone, riding amusement rides and karting on the purpose built Indy Circuit. With the added safety of bumpers, Children as young as 5 years can experience all the thrills of go karting in a safe and well organised day of fun and excitement. Next to the track is Side Show Alley with amusement rides and computer games that'll keep the kids busy for hours.

The general public can jump straight onto our European style Monte Carlo Circuit on which they can race Predator & Formula Karts against their mates or race the clock to set the day's best lap time. The experienced drivers get to race the awesome Schumacher race karts on the 1100m International Standard Le Mans Track. This the only hire track in Australia that offers you true racing experience on an international standard circuit.

Also check out our new blog for weekly offers and updates:

name: Peddells Thursday Island Tours
slogan: Linking the Cape to Torres Strait since 1980.
description:
Peddell's Thursday Island Tours is locally owned and operated and provides a regular Jetty to Jetty passenger ferry service between Thursday Island in Torres Strait and Seisia on Cape York Peninsula.  They also offer historic and scenic guided island bus tours. 
As Torres Strait tourism pioneers Peddells continue to set the standard of passenger services in the region. When travelling with Peddells you are assured of the most comfortable ride on board large modern vessels.  Visitors will experience an unrivaled introduction to the region with Peddells expert local tour guides and visit the most historically significant and scenic sites on Thursday Island.
Established in 1980 the fifth generation Torres Strait Peddell family and their team look forward to warmly welcoming you to their island home. For further information please visit www.peddellsferry.com.au

name: Port Stephens 4WD Tours
slogan: NUMBER ONE FOR SANDBOARDING AND 4WD TOURS ON THE STOCKTON SAND DUNES!!
description: Covering 78 sq.kilometres, the traditional home of the Worimi people is the largest mobile sand mass in the Southern Hemisphere. Within their expanse you will discover a host of fascinating stories that reveal much about our past. From 12,000 year old Aboriginal middens and the skeletal remains of shipwrecks to WW2 tank fortifications and the hidden, remote outpost of Tin City. Then, for the adventurous, enjoy the thrill of sand boarding down 60 degree slopes that are 30 metres high. Experiencing the vast dunes for the first time is truly AMAZING!!

name: Tasmania – The Gift Shop
slogan: Our homeware and gift product designs blend premium workmanship with the best in thoughtful, functional design principles, at a surprisingly great value price.
description:
We are woodwork and woodcraft specialists, however we cover a broad range of artisan works, including pottery, glass, jewellery, small batch liquor, chocolateer and fudge offerings, lavender products, soaps and creative homewares.

We stock an eclectic selection of handmade gifts from many of Tasmania's finest artisans, together with a range of Tasmanian themed products suiting a wide variety of tastes and budgets.

Our makers create a multitude of handmade gift lines and handcrafted homewares using quality, naturally occuring materials utilising time-proven techniques.

We also stock clothing and kids stuff available from a broad Tasmanian themed souvenir range.

name: Cleland Wildlife Park
description:
Ever wanted to hold a koala? At Cleland Wildlife Park you can!

Just 20 minutes drive from Adelaide, you can touch and feed captivating wildlife in this open range wildlife sanctuary.

Have your photo taken holding a koala, hand feed kangaroos and wander among Australian wildlife. Join animal keepers as they feed lorikeets, Tasmanian Devils, dingoes, water birds and other native animals.

At night the bush also comes to life. Accompany guides and share the night-time world of Australia’s intriguing and endangered animals including potoroos, bettongs and bandicoots. Wallabies and kangaroos also become more active and alert at night. Bookings essential.

Don’t miss out on the Ocean to Outback Interpretative Centre where South Australia’s landscapes are on display.

Cleland Wildlife Park is nestled within Cleland Conservation Park just three kilometres from Mount Lofty Summit.

Encounters with wildlife, licensed cafe and souvenir shop, ensures there’s something for everyone at Cleland!

name: Devonport Visitor Information Centre
slogan: Devonport, Spirit of Tasmania, Devonport Tasmania, Accommodation Devonport Tasmania, Devonport weather
description: The Devonport Visitor Information Centre is there to provide all of your informatoin needs if you are a visitor to Devonport. We can help you with Devonport accommodation, Devonport attractions and information about the region. There is plenty to do in Devonport whether you are here for a few hours before you board the Spirit of Tasmania or longer. We have special itineraries if you just want to kill a few hours before you depart or if you are looking for things to do in Devonport as a visitor.

name: Merimbula Visitor Information Centre
slogan: Merimbula with its great climate, pristine beaches and abundant natural beauty is an ideal location for your next holiday.
description: Bass and Flinders explored the Merimbula area in 1797 â?? and were the first of many â??visitors to be struck by the beauty of its waterways, and surrounding forests. While oysters are a popular and profitable industry today, the discovery of a large number of middens either side of the lake proves the original Aboriginal settlers were just as passionate about them! Close by are some of Australiaâ??s most significant national parks offering a range of nature experiences that draw visitors from all over the world. Merimbula buzzes with special events year round â?? the annual jazz festival, orchid shows, fishing competitions or the Merimbula Malibu or Classic wavesailing, kitesurfing and SUPs (stand up paddle), and food festivals. The Merimbula Boardwalk skirts the northern shores of the Top Lake section of Merimbula Lake and is a 3.5km stunning round trip, broken by a wildlife experiences on the way.  Or if youâ??re feeling a little more energetic, try standup paddleboarding in the protected lake waters, a local favourite. And, of course, there is wonderful seafood. Donâ??t miss out on award winning locally grown oysters and mussels.

name: Rockhampton Heritage Village
description: One of the most popular stops for travellers in Central Queensland is the Rockhampton Heritage Village. Set on 11 hectares of land, the village features a wide range of original and reproduction buildings, as well as memorabilia and artefacts portraying life in the region from the 1850s to the 1950s. Visitors can take a leisurely stroll and look through the school, wagon works, fire station, timber cutters camp, woolshed, cottages and more. There is also an impressive array of timepieces in the Hall of Clocks, a display of dolls and a great collection of vintage vehicles. Market days are held on Sundays every two months. Open daily 9am to 4pm. Closed public holidays. Last admission 3pm.

name: Summerland Farm
slogan: Taste the Region
description: Summerland House Farm is a beautiful working macadamia and avocado farm and popular tourist attraction, set on 172 acres on the Alstonville plateau in Northern NSW. As a business of House with No Steps, the farm creates opportunities for people with a disability. Here you will find a fully licensed cafÃ© and function centre, retail outlets such as regional gourmet foods and gifts, mini golf, tractors tours, a museum, kids playground and waterpark. Groups welcome. Guided tours available.

name: Devonport Regional Gallery
slogan: The Devonport Regional Gallery showcases a diverse program of exhibitions including in-house curated exhibitions, guest curated exhibitions and touring exhibitions.
description: The Devonport Regional Gallery aims to enhance understanding of visual art, craft and design through the delivery of a challenging, high quality and engaging exhibition and events program that promotes the work of Tasmanian artists.

name: House Of Anvers
description:
The House of Anvers at Latrobe in Tasmania’s north is a chocolate lovers’ heaven.
Hand-made chocolate truffles, chocolate oranges, fudge and praline, using fresh Tasmanian cream and butter, producing the world's finest chocolate and liqueurs.  
Igor Van Gerwen, the chocolate confectioner acquired his know-how from his birthplace, Belgium.
A selection box of truffles includes flavours such as kirsch, strawberry and Grand Marnier. Flavours that would dominate others -  ginger and mint,  are packed by themselves. A terrific light gift to take home, that's truly Tasmanian.
The House of Anvers is a real chocolate taste sensation and is located in the property known as Wyndarra Lodge, a stylish house (c.1931) set in 1.12 hectares of mature tree gardens. 
Anvers has viewing windows so you can see the factory in action; confectionery staff tempering, moulding and enrobing fine chocolates, truffles, pralines, fudge and more.
There is a small museum on the history of chocolate, and our coffee shop (open fire place, stained glass windows) specialises in chocolates, hot cocoa in many flavours, chocolate desserts and...more chocolate. French breakfast and light Tasmanian fare lunches are served, and a range of teas and espresso coffees for the morning and afternoon break.

description:
Family Entertainment Center, including Lasertag, Arcade, Pool Tables, Juke Box,  Redemption Games.

description: The Emu Ridge Eucalyptus Oil distillery and retail shop has been a popular Kangaroo Island tourist attraction since 1991, and we are now the only Eucalyptus Oil distillery in South Australia. We manufacture 100% pure Australian Eucalyptus Oil, which we sell along with a large range of associated products through our online store.

name: Nova Cruises
slogan: Locally owned and operated business offering wide range of scheduled and private charter cruises.
description: Nova Cruises Pty Ltd is a locally owned and operated business. Our vessels "Bay Connections 1" and "The Princess" operate from Newcastle Harbour offering a wide range of scheduled cruises including: Newcastle Harbour Luncheons, Twlight Dinner Cruises, Whale Watching, Cruises to Historic Morpeth, Hunter River Discovery Cruises, Hunter to Harbour History Tours, Bingo Afloat and private charters, weddings & events all departing from Lee Wharf pontoon Newcastle.

name: Kununurra Visitor Centre
slogan: Allow yourself the time
description:
Welcome to the Visitor Centre for Kununurra, the ideal base for exploring the magnificent East Kimberley region of WA.

With so many places to go and so much to see, the hardest part will be deciding whether to stay for one week or two in the East Kimberley. 

See natural wonders and rugged ridges and be awed by the magnificent Lake Argyle. 

From sparkling diamonds to barramundi fishing, Kununurra has it all.

name: Billabong Zoo, Koala and Wildlife Park
description:
For a wild day out you must visit Billabong Zoo, it’s the perfect family outing. The park boasts a wide variety of Australian and exotic animals and birds featuring their world renowned koala breeding centre. Be amazed as you learn from their friendly and informative keeper talks, Visit Reptopia, their house of reptiles and see the most venomous land snake on the planet.  Savour their delicious homemade treats and fresh ground coffee in the Zoo Cafe, or take home a special memento from the huge gift shop. 

There are animal presentations daily. Have your photo taken with a koala or dingo or watch the spider monkey or reptile shows. 

Entry to main building is free with access to the information centre, arts, souvenirs, crafts, gift shop and for refreshments in the zoo cafe. Entry fee applies for park entry.  There are free gas barbecues and picnic areas onsite.

name: Destination Southern Highlands
slogan: So Close, A World Away!
description:
Make the Southern Highlands your next short break destination, and you will find a treasure trove of destinational attractions, like award winning restaurants and wineries, magnificent gardens, rare antiques, authentic heritage and amazing natural wonders.
The Southern Highlands is a great place to relax, escape, unwind and rejuvenate, and is within a comfortable driving distance of Sydney, Canberra, the South Coast and Illawarra.
The Southern Highlands - So close, a world away!

name: Coffs City Skydivers
slogan: Coffs Harbour City Skydivers - tandem and solo parachuting jumps, training and extreme action!
description: Coffs City Skydivers is the largest and longest established skydiving centre on the Mid North Coast. We offer tandem skydives, training, corporate functions and merchandise.

name: Gold Coast Skydive
description:
Gold Coast Skydive provides the opportunity to skydive over the spectacular Gold Coast.
Experience a rush with a 45 second free fall
Take in unmatched views and scenery 
Free fall at 200km/h attached to an experienced tandem master. Plummet towards the earth and feel the adrenaline rush before your parachute opens. Take in the breathtaking views of the Gold Coast from the air and best of all you get to land on the beach.

A Tandem Skydive over the Gold Coasts amazing beaches is an experience of a lifetime. After a short training session of approximately 15 minutes covering the equipment, free fall techniques, how to exit the aircraft and what to expect, you will accompany your instructor to the aircraft which will be taking off from the international airport. Once inside the aircraft you will ascend to your exit height of 12,000 feet. While climbing you will be able to take in the amazing views of the Gold Coast. 

You will be securely harnessed to your instructor as you get ready for the rush of a lifetime! Your freefall will last approximately 45 seconds right over the beach. You whiz past huge white clouds on your rush back to earth. After reaching terminal velocity your instructor will deploy the parachute for a 4 to 5 minute float back to earth, the perfect opportunity to take in the awesome views of the gold coast. Your adventure concludes with a landing on the soft sandy beach at Kirra and the presentation of your Jump Certificate.

name: Oakvale Farm & Fauna World
description:
Set on 25 acres Oakvale Farm & Fauna World is 100% Australian owned and operated. At the farm you will find an endless menagerie of Australian native, domestic farm and exotic animals such as koalas, kangaroos, wombats, goats, sheep, rabbits, alligators and ostriches. Plus many, many more. 

Established in November 1979 by Jeff and Elaine Sansom and later passed down to their son Kent Sansom in 1995. Oakvale Farm & Fauna World has remained a family owned and operated business for more than 35yrs. 

Since 1979 the farm has undergone countless changes. The most recent of which is the Koala Breeding and Education Centre known as 'Koala Country'.

However, one thing remains the same is our commitment to providing an opportunity for our customers to learn about our native wildlife and how we can protect it.

We strive to provide a fun, safe, educational and value for money experience for the whole family. 

Oakvale Farm & Fauna World are proud to be Ecotourism Certified, TQUAL Accredited, ZAA members and have implemented an Environmental Management Plan as a part of our ongoing commitment to a sustainable future.

name: Dreamworld
slogan: Australia's Biggest Theme Park
description:
Australia's BIGGEST theme park, Dreamworld on the Gold Coast is bursting with happiness with over 50 rides and attractions to suit everyone from toddlers to thrill seekers and beyond.

Famous for having the highest, fastest and most impressive rides in the country, Dreamworld is home to the BIG9 thrill rides; TailSpin, The Claw, Buzz Saw, Tower of Terror II, Giant Drop, The Wipeout, Pandamonium, The Cyclone and Motocoaster.  Thrill seekers also love Zombie Evilution: The Battle for Kevil Hill- the most challenging laser combat maze in the southern hemisphere.

Worlds of fun for family and friends, Dreamworld is where toddlers can enjoy Wiggles World and  the DreamWorks Experience where famous movie characters from Madagascar, Shrek, Kung Fu Panda and Puss In Boots mingle with the crowd.  

Staying true to Dreamworld's promise to offer more adventures than anywhere else in Australia, it is also home to Tiger Island and Dreamworld Corroboree.   Only at Dreamworld can guests encounter the worlds largest interactive tiger facility at Tiger Island then see the world through Indigenous eyes at Dreamworld Corroboree home to 500 native animals and birds including koalas and kangaroos.
 
All in one MASSIVE location, Dreamworld's sister attraction is WhiteWater World.  Fun all-year-round from the Gold Coast's balmy warm summer through to the warmest water of any park in Winter (27 degrees), WhiteWater World offers thrilling slides and great family fun for everyone.  Enjoy the best of both worlds!  

For more information on Dreamworld and WhiteWater World phone us or visit our website.

name: Port Pirie Regional Tourism & Arts Centre
description:
Visit the Port Pirie Regional Tourism and Arts Centre, formerly the Port Pirie Railway Station and redeveloped to reflect Port Pirie's heritage, with architectural features and artworks interpreting the city's industrial, maritime, transport and agricultural history.

Get up close to the 'Longest White Pointer Shark Landed in South Australia'.

Take a miniature railway trip on the Pirie Rail Express, with two locomotives, the steam engine 'Elizabeth' and a diesel engine 'Lady Pirie' that travels a 1.7 kilometre trip to Broken Hill.

Don't miss taking a bus tour of the world's largest primary lead smelter, Nyrstar Port Pirie. And taste the flavours of local food produce and grab a few mementos from the Totally Loco Souvenir and Gift Shop.

It's just a sample of what you can experience in Port Pirie, 'the Friendly City'.

name: Sea Acres Rainforest Centre
description:
Sea Acres Rainforest Centre is an inspiring experience. Share the wonders of one of the largest remaining coastal rainforest reserves in New South Wales.

Enjoy the tranquil beauty of the elevated, accessible 1.3 kilometre rainforest boardwalk through pristine subtropical rainforest and relax in the Rainforest Cafe, serving delicious lunch, morning and afternoon teas. Boardwalk entry fee applies.

Take a guided tour with the friendly Sea Acres volunteer guides or explore the rainforest at your own pace. Specialised Aboriginal bush tucker tours are also offered on the third Saturday of the month. Bookings are essential. 

You can also get information about the mid North Coast National Parks, view eco-displays, changing art exhibitions and visit the gift shop selling a range of unique environmental products, gifts, crafts and educational toys and games.

name: Lake Macquarie City Art Gallery
description:
Lake Macquarie City Art Gallery is an exceptional cultural and tourist destination. Beautifully located on the shores of Lake Macquarie, the unique precinct embraces expansive leafy grounds, a sculpture park and an award-winning exhibition facility with a national reputation.

The gallery's innovative and relevant program ensures that every visit is a visual treat. Noteworthy touring shows alternate with lively gallery-curated exhibitions featuring nationally significant artists, many of whom share a connection with the Hunter. Strong and respectful Aboriginal projects and exhibitions are integrated within the program.

The gallery shop offers a unique selection of the highest quality handcrafted ceramics, glass, jewellery and textiles, as well as books, catalogues, cards, novelty items and exhibition-related merchandise. Featured are crafts people from the Hunter and Central Coast regions along with work by established and emerging craft practitioners from further afield.

Sharing the gallery's spectacular site is the celebrated Awaba House Restaurant Cafe.

name: Southern Yorke Peninsula Visitor Information Centre
Sea World Theme Park
description:
At Sea World you can make contact with marine life wonders and experience a whole world of amazing attractions, rides and shows at a Gold Coast theme park favourite! More than just a theme park, Sea World is committed to educating guests about the marine environment, and playing an active role in Australian marine research and rescue.


With its laid-back pace and a myriad of options, Sea World is the kind of theme park that will please the whole family. There are many high-octane rides with the rollercoaster, Pirate and the new Jet Rescue leading the thrills, but step back a gear and enjoy seal and dolphin shows, plus Sea World’s spectacular ski showcase. Swim with dolphins and sharks, plus enjoy polar bears in an up-close encounter.

name: SkyPoint Observation Deck
slogan: Experience 360 degree views at Australia's only beachside observation deck
description:
SkyPoint, located on level 77 of the Q1 building and 230 metres above ground provides a spectacular 360 degree view of the entire Gold Coast.  

Travel to the top in one of the World's fastest lifts in less than 43 seconds.

By day you can see breathtaking panoramic views from the surf to the hinterland and beyond. 

SkyPoint Bar & Cafe offers an extensive menu from coffee and cakes to delicious meals served throughout the day at various times.

At night experience the twinkling city lights and indulge in a decadent cocktail from SkyPoint Bar.

On Friday and Saturday nights, SkyPoint Bar features live DJ entertainment and morphs into the hottest, highest altitude bar on the Gold Coast

name: Tas Laser Skirmish

From humble beginnings nearly 30 years ago Funfields has developed into Melbourne's Favourite Theme Park with a host of quality attractions featuring a tantalising mix of both wet and dry rides  to guarantee a truly awesome day of outdoor family fun with Unlimited Rides ON ALL OUR ATTRACTIONS ALL DAY.
Everday's a funday @ Funfields!
Enjoy the Alpine Toboggan Slide, Go Karts, Swinging Pirate Ship and Bumper Boats or test your skills at the ALL NEW Treasure Cove Mini Golf Course.

If slides is more your thing then you're spoilt for choice at Funfields. The Blackout and Wipeout raft waterslides offer two exciting and very different experiences. Then there is the two Splashdown Waterslides and for the extreme thrill seekers, Typhoon, the World's Longest Pro Slide CannonBowl ride and the Kraken Racer which is a first for Australia!
We haven"t forgotten about our younger Funfielders who can enjoy the NEW Formula Fun Mini Go Karts, Snakes Alive - cup and saucer ride with a slithery twist, Burnout,  NEW Pony Express Carousel, the Berry Ferris Wheel and the Samba Balloon.

The Alice Springs School of the Air provides this educational service in an area of 1.3 million square kilometres. The Park was developed in the 1920s and 1930s by Spanish immigrant Jose Paronella, an early eco-tourism operator. Visitors are amazed to find amongst the many buildings, North Queensland's first privately owned hydro electric system and fountains fed by the 60 feet Mena Creek Falls. Jose planted 7000 trees enabling the inclusion of a self guided botanical tour into the visitor experience. After successfully operating until his death in 1948, the Park was lost for 45 years. It was rediscovered in 1993.

The experience includes the story of Jose Paronella's dream (Day tours) 45 minutes and the evening experience (the night light-up and tour) one hour. Entry is valid for 12 months and also includes one night in the camping and caravan park.

name: Gosford Regional Gallery And Edogawa Commemorative Garden
description:
The Gosford Regional Gallery is located on the shores of Caroline Bay in East Gosford. It is part of a complex that also includes the Gosford/Edogawa Commemorative Garden, the Arts Centre and the Caroline Bay Brasserie, Cafe and Function Centre.

The Gallery offers a diverse and stimulating exhibition program consisting of a range of local, national and international exhibitions of various media including painting, photography, sculpture, textiles, ceramics, and works on paper. 

The Garden, a generous gift from Gosford's sister city - Edogawa, covers an area of approximately 4,000 square metres and is presented as a traditional Japanese 'stroll garden' enclosed by a two metre high wall.  Pathways meander through various landscape settings with a tumbling stream and lake as the centrepiece.

A tea house and fish feeding pavilion overlook the main body of the lake.

Other features of the garden include a dry stone garden, timber footbridges, wisteria pergola and planting of pines, maples, cherries, azaleas, lotus and water lilies.

The Caroline Bay Brasserie is a fully licensed restaurant open for lunch daily and for dinner Thursday to Saturday nights.

Riversands Wines in St George is the perfect spot to enjoy a free wine tasting in their cosy cellar. Their lively free wine tastings will take your taste buds through the flavours of Western Queensland as you sip crisp, dry whites and popular reds, through to the rich flavours of their Golden Liqueur Muscat.

How about a sip of port from a Senators boot? A unique pottery gift range is their specialty. Tawny port filled pottery replicas such as the Condamine Bell, Senator Barnaby's Boots, Quart Pot and Fred Brophy’s Bozing boots feature in their range. Be sure to try the handmade grape jam and chutney while you visit!

Spend the morning or afternoon with family and friends in the outdoor garden cafe. Treat yourself and indulge in scones with jam and cream, mud cake, hot coffee or perhaps a cheese platter and wine as you overlook the vineyard – and create your own bush story in every glass.
